<ClerriLayout title="Messaging Playbook" section="messaging-playbook">

<div class="page-head">
  <div class="page-eyebrow">Channels & Budget · Messaging & Campaign Playbook</div>
  <h1 class="page-title">The actual copy. <em>Lift it and ship.</em></h1>
  <p class="page-sub">One core narrative, flexed across 8 buyer personas — real headlines, messages, and objection responses — plus a written SMB email cadence, a DSO ABM sequence, and a content slate. Less framework, more ammunition.</p>
</div>

<div class="page-body">

  <div class="takeaway">
    <span class="tk-lbl">Bottom line</span>
    <p>The spine is "<strong>Take your practice back from insurance — one patient at a time.</strong>" Villain: the insurance middleman. The trap: going it alone (DIY plans / PPO dependence). The escape: Clerri — structured, compliant, proven (7 of top 10 DSOs). Every persona below is that same story told in <em>their</em> language. Steal the copy directly; tune one line to voice; ship.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Messaging architecture — <em>one story, eight angles.</em></h2>
  <div style="overflow-x:auto">
  <table class="mtable">
    <thead><tr><th>Audience</th><th>What they actually care about</th><th>The angle</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Owner-dentist (SMB)</td><td>Autonomy, income, not fighting insurers</td><td>Emotional — take your practice back</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Office manager</td><td>Less admin, fewer claims, looking good to the doc</td><td>Operational relief</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Small-group operator</td><td>Consistency + growth without overhead</td><td>Scale without chaos</td></tr>
      <tr><td>DSO C-suite</td><td>EBITDA, same-store growth, enterprise value</td><td>The multiple expander</td></tr>
      <tr><td>CFO / RCM</td><td>Predictable revenue, write-off recovery, clean books</td><td>Forecastable recurring revenue</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Operations</td><td>Standardized rollout, painless implementation</td><td>Live in 30 days, every location</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Marketing leader</td><td>Patient acquisition, member growth, retention</td><td>The retention + acquisition engine</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Payer relations</td><td>Payer leverage, reimbursement, mix</td><td>Insurance independence</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  </div>

  <h2>SMB personas</h2>

  <h3>Owner-dentist <span class="pill pill-zest">SMB</span></h3>
  <div class="card persona">
    <p class="who"><strong>Who:</strong> clinician first, businessperson by necessity. Resents insurers eroding reimbursement + dictating care; fears losing patients if they drop a PPO; time-poor.</p>
    <p class="msg"><strong>Core message:</strong> "You became a dentist to treat patients — not to fight insurance companies for 60 cents on the dollar. Membership lets you take your practice back, one patient at a time, without going cash-only."</p>
    <p class="hooks"><strong>Headlines:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>"Fire your insurance company. Keep your patients."</li>
      <li>"You'll write off $3-6M to PPOs over your career. Here's the math on getting it back."</li>
      <li>"30% of dentists dropped a PPO last year. The ones who thrived had a membership plan ready."</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="proof"><strong>Proof that lands:</strong> 7 of top 10 DSOs run on Clerri; a membership patient produces ~$1,276/yr vs ~$469 cash <span class="vmono">(verify)</span>; SkyRidge 8x'd enrollment.</p>
    <p class="obj"><strong>Objection — "I'll lose my insured patients":</strong> "Membership isn't cash-only — it runs alongside insurance, and it's how you keep the patients you'd otherwise lose when you drop a plan. You set the fee schedule, not a payer."</p>
    <p class="chan"><strong>Reach them:</strong> Google search (high intent), dental podcasts, peer referral, email nurture.</p>
  </div>

  <h3>Office manager / front-office lead <span class="pill pill-zest">SMB</span></h3>
  <div class="card persona">
    <p class="who"><strong>Who:</strong> runs the chaos — scheduling, billing, claims, patient questions, staff turnover. Insurance admin is their daily pain. Wants less hassle and to look good to the dentist.</p>
    <p class="msg"><strong>Core message:</strong> "Membership means fewer claims to chase, fewer 'do you take my insurance?' calls, and patients who actually show up — and we make it turnkey so it's not one more thing on your plate."</p>
    <p class="hooks"><strong>Headlines:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>"Less insurance admin. More patients who show up."</li>
      <li>"The membership plan that runs itself — so you don't have to."</li>
      <li>"Enroll a member in 60 seconds. No claim to chase."</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="proof"><strong>Proof that lands:</strong> Bridge Pro auto-writes enrollments into the PMS (zero double-entry); support that actually answers the phone; turnkey enrollment flow.</p>
    <p class="obj"><strong>Objection — "I don't have time for another system":</strong> "That's exactly the point — Bridge Pro writes enrollments straight into your PMS, no double entry. Most offices spend less time on a member than on a single insurance claim."</p>
    <p class="chan"><strong>Reach them:</strong> AADOM (their professional home), email, in-office enablement, practice webinars.</p>
  </div>

  <h3>Small-group operator (2-9 locations) <span class="pill pill-zest">SMB</span></h3>
  <div class="card persona">
    <p class="who"><strong>Who:</strong> scaling past one chair, wears the operator hat, wants consistency across offices + growth without proportional headcount. Between solo and DSO.</p>
    <p class="msg"><strong>Core message:</strong> "Standardize membership across every location, see the numbers in one dashboard, and grow recurring revenue without growing your back office."</p>
    <p class="hooks"><strong>Headlines:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>"One membership plan. Every location. One dashboard."</li>
      <li>"Grow recurring revenue across your group — without growing your overhead."</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="proof"><strong>Proof that lands:</strong> multi-location support + analytics; 7 to 7 Dental scaled membership revenue past $4.5M <span class="vmono">(verify)</span>.</p>
    <p class="obj"><strong>Objection — "My locations all do things differently":</strong> "Clerri standardizes the plan and the enrollment flow while each location keeps its own fee schedule. Consistency where it matters, flexibility where it doesn't."</p>
    <p class="chan"><strong>Reach them:</strong> LinkedIn, group-practice events, case studies, light ABM.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>DSO / Enterprise buying committee</h2>
  <p style="color:var(--ink-soft);max-width:70ch">Same deal, five different people in the room — each needs the message in their own currency. This is where independent messaging matters most: a CFO and a CMO will kill or champion the deal for opposite reasons.</p>

  <h3>C-suite (CEO / COO) <span class="pill pill-wine">DSO</span></h3>
  <div class="card persona">
    <p class="msg"><strong>Core message:</strong> "Membership is same-store growth that compounds — more recurring revenue per location, less insurance dependence, higher enterprise value at exit. 7 of the top 10 DSOs already run it on Clerri."</p>
    <p class="hooks"><strong>Headlines:</strong> "The same-store growth lever your board is asking about." · "Recurring revenue is a multiple expander. Membership is how DSOs build it."</p>
    <p class="obj"><strong>Objection — "We're evaluating Subscribili":</strong> "Ask them to show a Denticon DSO at your scale that's live and fully enrolled — not just signed. We can. 7 of the top 10 already run on us." <span class="vmono">(battlecard)</span></p>
    <p class="chan"><strong>Reach them:</strong> ABM, ADSO + exec events, board/peer referral, founder-led content.</p>
  </div>

  <h3>CFO / RCM / revenue-cycle <span class="pill pill-wine">DSO</span></h3>
  <div class="card persona">
    <p class="msg"><strong>Core message:</strong> "Membership converts unpredictable, written-down insurance revenue into predictable recurring cash — and Clerri posts it to your ledger, so your production reporting stays clean."</p>
    <p class="hooks"><strong>Headlines:</strong> "Turn insurance write-offs into revenue you can forecast." · "Membership revenue that actually shows up in your production reports."</p>
    <p class="obj"><strong>Objection (Plan Forward FUD) — "Doesn't ledger write-back hurt my production numbers at sale?":</strong> "The opposite — recurring membership revenue is a premium to buyers because it's predictable. Accurate ledger posting makes it visible and properly valued. Leaving it off-ledger creates reconciliation gaps that understate your practice."</p>
    <p class="chan"><strong>Reach them:</strong> ABM, Becker's, finance-leader content, an ROI calculator.</p>
  </div>

  <h3>Operations (VP / Director) <span class="pill pill-wine">DSO</span></h3>
  <div class="card persona">
    <p class="msg"><strong>Core message:</strong> "Clerri rolls out across all your locations with a proven implementation playbook — live with your first member in 30 days, standardized everywhere, without burdening your offices."</p>
    <p class="hooks"><strong>Headlines:</strong> "Membership, standardized across every location — live in 30 days." · "The rollout that doesn't blow up your offices."</p>
    <p class="obj"><strong>Objection — "Onboarding 200 locations sounds brutal":</strong> "We have dedicated data-migration and installation teams and a 30-day-to-first-member target. Ask a competitor to show a comparable-scale rollout that's live and enrolled."</p>
    <p class="chan"><strong>Reach them:</strong> ABM, ops peer networks, implementation case studies.</p>
  </div>

  <h3>Marketing leader (CMO / Director) <span class="pill pill-wine">DSO</span></h3>
  <div class="card persona">
    <p class="msg"><strong>Core message:</strong> "Membership is your recurring-revenue retention engine and a patient-acquisition magnet — and we hand your team the patient-facing content and the directory demand that fills your chairs."</p>
    <p class="hooks"><strong>Headlines:</strong> "The retention engine your CMO dashboard is missing." · "Turn your locations into a patient-acquisition flywheel."</p>
    <p class="obj"><strong>Objection — "My team is stretched thin":</strong> "That's why we provide turnkey patient-education and enablement content your offices deploy — you get the member growth without building it from scratch."</p>
    <p class="chan"><strong>Reach them:</strong> LinkedIn, marketing-leader content, co-marketing.</p>
  </div>

  <h3>Payer relations / payer strategy <span class="pill pill-wine">DSO</span></h3>
  <div class="card persona">
    <p class="msg"><strong>Core message:</strong> "Membership reduces your dependence on payers — shifting volume to a revenue stream you control, which strengthens your hand at the negotiating table."</p>
    <p class="hooks"><strong>Headlines:</strong> "Less leverage for the payers. More for you." · "Build the revenue stream that isn't at the mercy of a fee-schedule cut."</p>
    <p class="obj"><strong>Objection — "We can't just drop payers":</strong> "You don't — membership runs alongside. But every member is a patient whose economics you control, which reduces payer concentration risk over time."</p>
    <p class="chan"><strong>Reach them:</strong> ABM, payer-strategy content, finance/ops events.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>SMB email cadence — <em>written, ready to load.</em></h2>
  <p style="color:var(--ink-soft);max-width:70ch">Triggered by a demo request or content download. Informational → demo. Tune voice, drop into HubSpot. (Replaces 7knots' generic templates.)</p>
  <div class="card seq">
    <p><span class="day">Day 0</span> <strong>Subject: The $3-6M question every practice owner should run</strong><br/>Over a 30-year career, the average practice writes off $3-6M to PPO adjustments. That's not a line item — that's a second house, a kid's college, an earlier retirement. Membership won't replace insurance overnight, but it starts clawing that margin back, one patient at a time. Here's the 2-minute version of how. [link]</p>
    <p><span class="day">Day 3</span> <strong>Subject: What 30% of dentists did last quarter</strong><br/>Nearly 30% of dentists dropped at least one insurance network last year. The ones who came out ahead didn't go cash-only — they had a membership plan ready to catch those patients. The ones who didn't lost the patients. Which group do you want to be in? [link]</p>
    <p><span class="day">Day 7</span> <strong>Subject: "But won't I lose patients?" — the honest answer</strong><br/>It's the first thing every dentist asks, so here's the straight version: membership runs <em>alongside</em> insurance, not instead of it. It's the safety net for the patients you'd otherwise lose to a dropped plan or no coverage — and you set the fee schedule. Here's how practices structure it. [link]</p>
    <p><span class="day">Day 12</span> <strong>Subject: How SkyRidge 8x'd enrollment without a sales team</strong><br/>SkyRidge didn't hire salespeople or retrain the front desk. They made membership turnkey — and grew enrollment 8x. The mechanics are simpler than you'd think, and they're the same ones we'd set up for you. [case study link] <span class="vmono">(verify stat)</span></p>
    <p><span class="day">Day 18</span> <strong>Subject: 15 minutes to see your numbers</strong><br/>You've seen the why. Want to see what it looks like for <em>your</em> practice? 15 minutes, your patient mix, your real numbers — no pitch deck. [book a time]</p>
  </div>

  <h2>DSO ABM sequence — <em>multi-touch, multi-channel.</em></h2>
  <div class="card seq">
    <p><strong>Structure (per target account, committee-aware):</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Touch 1 — email to CFO/RCM:</strong> the write-off-recovery angle (below).</li>
      <li><strong>Touch 2 — LinkedIn connect + comment</strong> on the C-suite contact (same week), no pitch.</li>
      <li><strong>Touch 3 — value send:</strong> a relevant DSO case study or the ROI calculator to Ops.</li>
      <li><strong>Touch 4 — the "live and enrolled" challenge</strong> to C-suite (the Subscribili counter).</li>
      <li><strong>Touch 5 — break-up / "worth a look?"</strong> with the 7-of-top-10 proof.</li>
    </ul>
    <p style="margin-top:0.75rem"><strong>Touch 1, written (CFO/RCM):</strong><br/>Subject: turning [DSO]'s PPO write-offs into forecastable revenue<br/><br/>[Name] — most DSO finance leaders I talk to are sitting on millions in annual PPO write-offs they treat as fixed. They're not. Membership converts a slice of that into predictable recurring revenue that posts to the ledger (so it shows up correctly in production reporting, not off in a side system). 7 of the top 10 DSOs already run it on Clerri. Worth 20 minutes to model what it'd look like across [DSO]'s locations?</p>
  </div>

